&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 6 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is a fixed term post as a band 5 staff nurse on the Special Care Baby Unit at the Princess of Wales Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an existing or a newly qualified staff nurse who would be interested in applying to join our team on SCBU at the Princess of Wales Hospital, we would love you to join us. We are committed and passionate about delivering evidence based, individualised, family centered care to all our babies and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires the ability to establish good relationships with parents and the extended family. To communicate effectively with the multidisciplinary team. To be able to deliver a high standard of skilled care in the acute setting within the health board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Baker - Interim Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
